[{"meta": {"name": "0165364.xml"}, "text": "Oberfinanzdirektion Frankfurt am Main S-1988 A - 37 - St II 24EStK F\u00f6rdG card 14F\u00f6rdG: 4F\u00f6rdG: 4/1 / 2EStG: 2 / 7BFH judgment IV R 59/95 v"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165364.xml"}, "text": "13 2 1997 BFH / NV 1997 635 FG Brandenburg judgment 2 K 1176/94 v"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165364.xml"}, "text": "21 6 1995 EFG 1995 999 Utilization of special depreciation according to the Aid Area Act; Binding to the exercise of the right to choose according to \u00a7 4 Paragraph 1 Sentence 2 F\u00f6rdG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165364.xml"}, "text": "of \u00a7\u00a7 2 and 3 Funding Act can be used in the year the investment is concluded and in the following four years (benefit period)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165364.xml"}, "text": "The beneficiary can therefore choose, in each year of the beneficiary period, whether and to what extent to claim the total allowable special depreciation"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165364.xml"}, "text": "To exercise the right to choose whether to claim the annual amount of special depreciation within the benefit period, the BFH decided in its judgment of 13 February 1997 (BFH / NV 1997 p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165364.xml"}, "text": "635) commented"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165364.xml"}, "text": "In this regard, he has the decision of the Finance Court of the State of Brandenburg of 21 June 1995 (EFG 1995 p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165364.xml"}, "text": "999) confirms that the beneficiary cannot change a final assessment by exercising the right to vote otherwise"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165364.xml"}, "text": "Thereafter, exercising the right to vote is not bound to a deadline"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165364.xml"}, "text": "However, if the beneficiary has exercised his right to choose in the income tax return and has been assessed for income tax as a result, his right to choose has been exhausted"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165364.xml"}, "text": "The beneficiary is bound by the choice made due to the validity of the tax assessment"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165364.xml"}, "text": "In this respect, the substantive right to choose is limited by the procedural institute of final force, but also by the principle of section taxation in accordance with Section 2 (7) EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165364.xml"}, "text": "The regulation of \u00a7 4 F\u00f6rdG also does not indicate the meaning and purpose that the exercise of the right to vote also or precisely the breach of the validity or the basic principle of section taxation i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165364.xml"}, "text": "of Section 2, Paragraph 7 of the Income Tax Act, since the decision on the use of the special depreciation is solely the responsibility of the beneficiary"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165364.xml"}, "text": "Thus, the beneficiary bears the risk that, once the income tax assessment has become final, exercising another option in the form of a different distribution of the special depreciation could turn out to be more favorable"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165364.xml"}, "text": "The use of the option granted in accordance with Section 4 Paragraph 1 Clause 2 of the Funding Act precludes a change in the final tax assessment for this assessment period"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165364.xml"}, "text": "This also applies if the requested change is a correction to the detriment of the beneficiary"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165364.xml"}, "text": "A change in the final tax assessment requested by the beneficiary by exercising the right to vote elsewhere must therefore be rejected"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165364.xml"}, "text": "The BFH is with the o"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165364.xml"}, "text": "Decision of 13 2 1997 followed his case law on the comparable option under Section 7b EStG (cf."}, {"meta": {"name": "0165364.xml"}, "text": "BFH judgment of 10 10 1969 BStBl 1970 II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165364.xml"}, "text": "63; BFH judgment of 18 December 1973 BStBl 1974 II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165364.xml"}, "text": "319; BFH judgment of 25 February 1992 BStBl 1992 II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165364.xml"}, "text": "621)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165364.xml"}, "text": "There are therefore no concerns if, if necessary, in addition to the above"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165364.xml"}, "text": "Decision of the Finance Court of the State of Brandenburg of June 21, 1995 and that of the BFH of February 13, 1997, reference is also made to the BFH case law on \u00a7 7b EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165364.xml"}, "text": "Since the BFH in its decision of 13.2.1997 expressly only fails to change the exercise of the right to vote because of the fact that the tax assessment has already entered into force, it is conversely possible for the beneficiary to exercise the right to vote in other ways if the assessment of the tax is subject to review in accordance with Section 164 AO or with regard to the special depreciation according to the development area law provisionally according to \u00a7 165 AO"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165364.xml"}, "text": "--- Accounting Tax support laws Income tax / wage tax / church tax Hesse Kw / 98/27 // Binding, option, special depreciation, F\u00f6rdG //"}]